commit.message: Update swagger-ui to v3.18.0
Make the name of the Blueprint configurable

Fixed string concatenation on OAuth2 redirect url

Redirect URLs  are often compared strictly. Flask's `request` ends in / by default, so that would result in /api/docs//oauth2-redirect.html (note double slash). This fix will cause the url to be correctly generated, regardless of the presence of a trainling slash on request.base_url.

Fixed string concatenation on OAuth2 redirect url

Redirect URLs  are often compared strictly. Flask's `request` ends in / by default, so that would result in /api/docs//oauth2-redirect.html (note double slash). This fix will cause the url to be correctly generated, regardless of the presence of a trainling slash on request.base_url.

commit.message:
Mark the module as not zip safe.

The template finder code in Flask doesn't handle zipped eggs well,
and thus won't find index.template.html.  This makes the module
crash when attempting to load the UI.
Use the proper config object when looking for oauth redirect URL.
